<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Bootstrap 4 Nested Media Task</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@4.6.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <style>
        body { background-color: #f8f9fa; padding: 40px 0; }
        .comment-section { max-width: 700px; margin: auto; background: white; padding: 25px; border-radius: 10px; box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.05); }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
    <div class="comment-section">
        <h4 class="mb-4">Discussion Thread</h4>

        <div class="media">
            <img src="https://picsum.photos/id/1027/64/64" class="mr-3 rounded-circle" alt="User Avatar">
            <div class="media-body">
                <h5 class="mt-0">Alex Rivera</h5>
                <p>The new Bootstrap 4 utility classes have significantly reduced the amount of custom CSS I need to write. Has anyone tried nesting media objects for comment sections yet?</p>

                <div class="media mt-3 border-left pl-3">
                    <a class="pr-3" href="#">
                        <img src="https://picsum.photos/id/1005/64/64" class="rounded-circle" alt="User Avatar">
                    </a>
                    <div class="media-body">
                        <h5 class="mt-0">Sarah Chen</h5>
                        <p>Yes! It's incredibly efficient. I usually add a small left border or padding to visually distinguish the reply from the original post.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.5.1.slim.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@4.6.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>

</body>
</html>
